  <description><![CDATA[<p>Complete your Lapland trip and stay in the stunning arctic surroundings of <a data-udi="umb://document/cc68d9ee210a4063af0a51552472263c" href="/{localLink:umb://document/cc68d9ee210a4063af0a51552472263c}" title="Yllas">Ylläs</a> in one of these Ylläsrinne Cabins. Dotted around the pretty village of Ylläsrinne amongst the snowy trees, you'll have plenty of space to play in the snow and enjoy the natural beauty of the untouched landscape.</p>
<h2>Fantastic for families, large or small</h2>
<p>These Ylläsrinne cabins are the ideal base for an Inghams <a data-udi="umb://document/f83de191792e4f76a2b62b60cd414e3a" href="/{localLink:umb://document/f83de191792e4f76a2b62b60cd414e3a}" title="Santa Breaks">Santa Break</a>. The smaller chocolate-box cabins are perfect for small families whilst the bigger detached cabins are well suited to larger groups - so there'll be lots of opportunities for quality time and fun together. And when you're not out searching for Santa or exploring Lapland on one of our exciting excursions, you can look forward to getting back to your cabin to cosy up by the fire or relaxing in a sauna.</p>
<h2>Specially selected cabins </h2>
<p>These cabins are full of charm and character,  furnished in a cosy Finnish style. The traditional Finnish cabins are dotted around the wintery woodland of the Arctic Circle. You'll get to experience the remote winter wonderland of Lapland first hand, whilst being within walking distance of the Ylläsrinne Hotel, the meeting point for your <a data-udi="umb://document/bda83b0ac78e4ae8aa3f5206e06059da" href="/{localLink:umb://document/bda83b0ac78e4ae8aa3f5206e06059da}" title="Lapland Safaris &amp; Excursions">excursions and safaris</a>.</p>
<h2>Food and drink </h2>
<p>We've taken care of the dining arrangements, with breakfast and dinner included at the neighbouring Ylläsrinne Hotel. You can also choose to have lunch here as an optional add-on. Head to the dining room for a buffet of warm, hearty food to keep you going after days out in the snow exploring Finnish Lapland. </p>]]></description>
